00:28:42.250 --> 00:28:46.039
Okay, so not surprisingly the
center of mass of this is not

00:28:46.039 --> 00:28:49.306
halfway to the other end,
but two-thirds of the way

00:28:49.306 --> 00:28:52.769
because it's top heavy;
this side of it is heavier.

00:28:52.769 --> 00:28:57.467
This is the level of calculus
you should be able to do in this

00:28:57.467 --> 00:29:00.240
course, be able to take some
body,

00:29:00.240 --> 00:29:03.799
slice it up in some fashion,
and find the location of the

00:29:03.799 --> 00:29:06.958
center of mass.
You combine symmetry arguments

00:29:06.958 --> 00:29:09.697
with actual calculation.
For this sliver,

00:29:09.697 --> 00:29:12.340
by symmetry,
you know the center of mass is

00:29:12.340 --> 00:29:15.109
at the center,
you don't waste your time,

00:29:15.109 --> 00:29:18.087
but then when you add these
guys there is no further

00:29:18.087 --> 00:29:21.410
symmetry you can use;
you have to do the actual work.

00:29:21.410 --> 00:29:28.287
So, what have I done so far?
What I've done is point out to

00:29:28.287 --> 00:29:31.235
you that when you work with
extended bodies,

00:29:31.235 --> 00:29:34.519
or more than one body,
we can now treat the entire

00:29:34.519 --> 00:29:37.482
body, replace the body by a
single point for certain

00:29:37.482 --> 00:29:39.993
purposes.
The single point is called a

00:29:39.993 --> 00:29:42.908
center of mass,
where it imagines all the mass

00:29:42.908 --> 00:29:45.369
concentrated at the center of
mass.

00:29:45.369 --> 00:29:48.380
So, you have created a brand
new entity which is fictitious.

00:29:48.380 --> 00:29:50.240
It has a mass equal to total
mass.

00:29:50.240 --> 00:29:53.830
It has a location equal to the
center of mass,

00:29:53.830 --> 00:29:57.500
and it moves in response to the
total force.

00:29:57.500 --> 00:30:01.250
And it's not aware of internal
forces, and that's what we want

00:30:01.250 --> 00:30:05.953
to exploit.
I already gave you a clue as to

00:30:05.953 --> 00:30:13.004
what the implications are,
but let me now take a thorough

00:30:13.004 --> 00:30:19.299
analysis of this basic equation
MR..= F.

00:30:19.299 --> 00:30:21.750
We're just going to analyze the
consequence.

00:30:21.750 --> 00:30:24.569
So there are several cases you
can consider.

00:30:24.569 --> 00:30:32.472
Case one:
F external not equal to

00:30:32.472 --> 00:30:33.160
0.

00:30:38.549 --> 00:30:41.202
So, these are two bodies
subject to mutual force and to

00:30:41.202 --> 00:30:43.461
an outside force,
but the simplest example I've

00:30:43.461 --> 00:30:46.556
already given to you -- but I'll
repeat it -- we're not going to

00:30:46.556 --> 00:30:48.755
do this in great detail.
We all know,

00:30:48.755 --> 00:30:51.839
if I fire a point mass like
this, it will do that.

00:30:51.839 --> 00:30:55.705
What I'm now telling you is,
if I take a complex body made

00:30:55.705 --> 00:30:58.622
of 20,000 parts,
all connected to each other

00:30:58.622 --> 00:31:01.807
pushing and pulling,
if you fling that crazy thing

00:31:01.807 --> 00:31:05.030
in the air it'll do all kinds of
gyrations and jiggling as it

00:31:05.030 --> 00:31:07.885
moves around.
But if you found its center of

00:31:07.885 --> 00:31:11.477
mass, the center of mass will
follow simply a parabola,

00:31:11.477 --> 00:31:15.069
because the external force on
it is just Mg.

00:31:15.069 --> 00:31:18.826
So, it'll be MR..= mg
and that's just motion with

00:31:18.826 --> 00:31:22.036
constant acceleration in the
y direction,

00:31:22.036 --> 00:31:24.700
and it's just a projectile
problem.

00:31:24.700 --> 00:31:27.393
And I repeat once more,
for emphasis,

00:31:27.393 --> 00:31:30.759
that if this object broke into
two objects,

00:31:30.759 --> 00:31:34.154
typically what'll happen is one
will fly there and one will land

00:31:34.154 --> 00:31:37.334
here, but at every instant if
you found their center of mass

00:31:37.334 --> 00:31:40.190
you will find it proceeds as if
nothing happened.

00:31:40.190 --> 00:31:42.133
For example,
if you have an explosive device

00:31:42.133 --> 00:31:44.619
that blows them apart,
and the pieces are all flying,

00:31:44.619 --> 00:31:48.438
but that's just coming from one
part of the piece pushing on

00:31:48.438 --> 00:31:51.630
another part of the piece,
but those forces are of no

00:31:51.630 --> 00:31:53.952
interest to us.
As far as the external force

00:31:53.952 --> 00:31:57.106
goes, it is still gravity so the
center of mass will continue

00:31:57.106 --> 00:31:58.789
traveling.
Beyond that,

00:31:58.789 --> 00:32:02.620
I'm not going to do too much
with this thing.

00:32:02.620 --> 00:32:10.150
So let me now go to Case II.
Case II.

00:32:10.150 --> 00:32:15.190
If you want, case 2a.
F external is equal to 0.

00:32:15.190 --> 00:32:19.190
What does it mean if F
external is 0?

00:32:19.190 --> 00:32:24.438
That means this is 0.
That means MR..

00:32:24.438 --> 00:32:37.431
= 0, that means MR.
is a constant because it's not

00:32:37.431 --> 00:32:42.920
changing.
Who is this MR.?

00:32:42.920 --> 00:32:46.123
What does it stand for?
Well, it looks like the

00:32:46.123 --> 00:32:49.148
following.
If you take a single particle

00:32:49.148 --> 00:32:52.263
of mass m,
and velocity x.,

00:32:52.263 --> 00:32:55.931
we use the symbol p,
maybe I've never used it before

00:32:55.931 --> 00:32:57.950
in the course,
and that's called the momentum.

00:33:03.579 --> 00:33:06.909
The momentum of a body is this
peculiar combination of mass and

00:33:06.909 --> 00:33:10.425
velocity.
In fact, in terms of momentum

00:33:10.425 --> 00:33:14.626
we may write Newton's law.
Instead of saying it's

00:33:14.626 --> 00:33:16.841
mdv/dt,
which is ma,

00:33:16.841 --> 00:33:20.063
you can also write it as
d by dt of

00:33:20.063 --> 00:33:23.196
mv,
because m is a constant

00:33:23.196 --> 00:33:27.237
and you can take it inside the
derivative, and that we can

00:33:27.237 --> 00:33:30.678
write as dp/dt.
Sometimes, instead of saying

00:33:30.678 --> 00:33:32.585
force is mass times
acceleration,

00:33:32.585 --> 00:33:36.279
people often say "force is the
rate of change of momentum."

00:33:36.279 --> 00:33:40.833
The rate at which the momentum
of a body is changing is the

00:33:40.833 --> 00:33:43.632
applied force.
So, if I've not introduced to

00:33:43.632 --> 00:33:46.079
you the notion of momentum,
well, here it is.

00:33:46.079 --> 00:33:49.419
So, if you think about it that
way, this looks like the

00:33:49.419 --> 00:33:52.916
momentum of the center of mass,
and we are told the momentum of

00:33:52.916 --> 00:33:55.640
the center of mass does not
change if there are no external

00:33:55.640 --> 00:33:57.776
forces.
But the momentum of the center

00:33:57.776 --> 00:34:00.832
of mass has a very simple
interpretation in terms of the

00:34:00.832 --> 00:34:03.110
parts that make up the center of
mass;

00:34:03.110 --> 00:34:06.640
let's see what it is.
Let's go back here.

00:34:06.640 --> 00:34:09.677
Remember, let me just take two
bodies and you will get the

00:34:09.677 --> 00:34:11.681
idea;
it's m_1 +

00:34:11.681 --> 00:34:14.659
m_2,
which is total M,

00:34:14.659 --> 00:34:17.638
and let's take just one
dimension when it's

00:34:17.638 --> 00:34:22.035
m_1x_1.+
m_2x_2.

00:34:22.035 --> 00:34:25.510
over m_1 +
m_2;

00:34:25.510 --> 00:34:30.908
that is what Mx. is.
So, m_1 +

00:34:30.908 --> 00:34:34.036
m_2 cancels here,
and you find this is just

00:34:34.036 --> 00:34:36.269
p_1 +
p_2.

00:34:36.269 --> 00:34:41.217
Let's use the symbol capital
P for momentum of the

00:34:41.217 --> 00:34:44.686
center of mass.
So, the momentum of the center

00:34:44.686 --> 00:34:48.159
of mass is the sum of the
momentum of the two parts,

00:34:48.159 --> 00:34:51.573
but what you're learning is --
so let me write it one more time

00:34:51.573 --> 00:34:53.719
-- if F eternal is equal
to 0,

00:34:53.719 --> 00:34:57.762
then p_1 +
p_2 does not

00:34:57.762 --> 00:34:59.330
change with time.

00:35:04.489 --> 00:35:07.516
This is a very,
very basic and fundamental

00:35:07.516 --> 00:35:11.796
property, and it's in fact
another result that survives all

00:35:11.796 --> 00:35:15.929
the revolutions of relativity
and quantum mechanics,

00:35:15.929 --> 00:35:19.440
where what I've said for two
bodies is true for ten bodies;

00:35:19.440 --> 00:35:21.989
you just do the summation over
more terms.

00:35:21.989 --> 00:35:24.410
So, let me say in words what
I'm saying.

00:35:24.410 --> 00:35:28.382
Take a collection of bodies.
At a given instant everything

00:35:28.382 --> 00:35:31.406
is moving;
it's got its own velocity and

00:35:31.406 --> 00:35:34.179
its momentum,
add up all the momenta.

00:35:34.179 --> 00:35:35.849
If you had one dimension,
just add the numbers.

00:35:35.849 --> 00:35:37.700
If in two dimensions,
add the vectors;

00:35:37.700 --> 00:35:40.686
you get a total momentum.
That total momentum does not

00:35:40.686 --> 00:35:43.949
change if there are no outside
forces acting on it.

00:35:43.949 --> 00:35:49.199
So, a classic example is two
people are standing on ice.

00:35:49.199 --> 00:35:53.645
Their total momentum is 0 to
begin with, and the ice is

00:35:53.645 --> 00:35:57.019
incapable of any force along the
plane.

00:35:57.019 --> 00:35:59.369
It's going to support you
vertically against gravity,

00:35:59.369 --> 00:36:02.170
but if it's frictionless it
cannot do anything in the plane.

00:36:02.170 --> 00:36:04.943
Then, the claim is that if you
and I are standing and we push

00:36:04.943 --> 00:36:06.699
against each other and we fly
apart,

00:36:06.699 --> 00:36:10.888
my momentum has to be exactly
the opposite of your momentum,

00:36:10.888 --> 00:36:13.869
because initially yours plus
mine was 0;

00:36:13.869 --> 00:36:17.619
that cannot change because
there are no external forces.

00:36:17.619 --> 00:36:19.837
If two particles are pushing
against each other,

00:36:19.837 --> 00:36:22.150
they can only do so without
changing the total.

00:36:26.320 --> 00:36:28.639
Okay, so p_1 +
p_2 does not

00:36:28.639 --> 00:36:31.309
change, and here's another
context in which it's important.

00:36:31.309 --> 00:36:33.519
Suppose there is a mass
m_1,

00:36:33.519 --> 00:36:35.929
going with some velocity
v_1,

00:36:35.929 --> 00:36:38.339
and here's the second mass
m_2,

00:36:38.339 --> 00:36:40.800
going with some velocity
v_2;

00:36:40.800 --> 00:36:42.948
they collide.
When they collide,

00:36:42.948 --> 00:36:45.964
all kinds of things can happen.
I mean, m_1

00:36:45.964 --> 00:36:47.856
may bump its head on that and
come backwards,

00:36:47.856 --> 00:36:50.350
or it could be a heavy object
that pushes everything in the

00:36:50.350 --> 00:36:53.039
forward direction,
or at the end of the day you

00:36:53.039 --> 00:36:55.771
will have some
m_1 going with

00:36:55.771 --> 00:36:58.199
a new velocity
v_1',

00:36:58.199 --> 00:37:01.381
and m_2 going
with a new velocity

00:37:01.381 --> 00:37:04.489
v_2'.
But what I'm telling you is

00:37:04.489 --> 00:37:07.359
that m_1
v_1 + m_2

00:37:07.359 --> 00:37:10.228
v_2 will be equal
to m_1

00:37:10.228 --> 00:37:13.500
v_1' + m_2
v_2‘.

00:37:13.500 --> 00:37:16.210
In a collision,
of course, one block exerts a

00:37:16.210 --> 00:37:19.537
force on the other block,
and the other block exerts an

00:37:19.537 --> 00:37:23.211
opposite force on this block,
and that's the reason why even

00:37:23.211 --> 00:37:26.329
though individually the momenta
could be very different,

00:37:26.329 --> 00:37:29.890
finally the momenta will add up
to the same total.

00:37:29.890 --> 00:37:34.611
Here's a simple example;
you can show that if this mass

00:37:34.611 --> 00:37:38.652
and that mass are equal,
and say this one is at rest,

00:37:38.652 --> 00:37:42.408
that one comes and hits this.
You can show under certain

00:37:42.408 --> 00:37:45.483
conditions this one will come to
rest and this will start moving

00:37:45.483 --> 00:37:48.313
with the speed of the--the
target will move at the speed of

00:37:48.313 --> 00:37:51.050
the projectile.
So, momenta of individual

00:37:51.050 --> 00:37:53.512
objects have changed.
One was moving before,

00:37:53.512 --> 00:37:55.090
it is not moving;
one was at rest,

00:37:55.090 --> 00:37:57.270
it's moving,
but when you add up the total,

00:37:57.270 --> 00:37:59.855
it doesn't change.
This is called the Law of

00:37:59.855 --> 00:38:03.757
Conservation of Momentum.
So, that's so important I'm

00:38:03.757 --> 00:38:07.930
just going to write it down here
one more time.

00:38:11.579 --> 00:38:16.846
And the basic result is,
if external forces are 0,

00:38:16.846 --> 00:38:20.930
then p_1 +
p_2 +

00:38:20.930 --> 00:38:25.924
p_3 and so on,
"before" will be

00:38:25.924 --> 00:38:29.324
p_1' +
p_2' +

00:38:29.324 --> 00:38:32.530
p_3',
and so on,

00:38:32.530 --> 00:38:39.530
where this means "before" and
that means "after," .

00:38:39.530 --> 00:38:42.789
When is "before" and when is
"after."

00:38:42.789 --> 00:38:45.460
Pick any two times in the life
of these particles,

00:38:45.460 --> 00:38:47.750
it's like Law of Conservation
of Energy,

00:38:47.750 --> 00:38:50.043
where we said E_1
= E_2,

00:38:50.043 --> 00:38:52.199
there 1 and 2 stood for
"before" and "after."

00:38:52.199 --> 00:38:55.141
Well, here we cannot use 1 and
2 for "before" and "after"

00:38:55.141 --> 00:38:57.610
because 1 and 2 and 3 are
labeling particles.

00:38:57.610 --> 00:39:00.763
So, the "before" quantities are
written without a prime,

00:39:00.763 --> 00:39:03.860
and the "after" quantities are
written with a prime.

00:39:03.860 --> 00:39:08.648
Everybody follow this?
It's very important you follow

00:39:08.648 --> 00:39:12.044
this statement and follow the
conditions under which it's

00:39:12.044 --> 00:39:14.619
valid.
There cannot be external forces.

00:39:14.619 --> 00:39:16.689
For example,
in the collision of these two

00:39:16.689 --> 00:39:19.415
masses, if there is friction
between the blocks and the

00:39:19.415 --> 00:39:21.347
table,
you can imagine they collide

00:39:21.347 --> 00:39:23.489
and they both come to rest after
a while.

00:39:23.489 --> 00:39:26.360
Originally, they had momentum
and finally they don't.

00:39:26.360 --> 00:39:28.334
What happened?
Well, here you have an

00:39:28.334 --> 00:39:30.897
explanation, namely,
the force of friction was an

00:39:30.897 --> 00:39:34.409
external force acting on them.
What I'm saying is that if the

00:39:34.409 --> 00:39:37.501
only force on each block is the
one due to each other,

00:39:37.501 --> 00:39:40.010
then the total momentum will
not change.

00:39:40.010 --> 00:39:46.239
So, the case that I considered,
2a, was external force equal to

00:39:46.239 --> 00:39:51.163
0, but center of mass was
moving, because it had a

00:39:51.163 --> 00:39:53.582
momentum.
Then, the claim is that

00:39:53.582 --> 00:39:57.327
momentum will not change.
I'm coming to the last case,

00:39:57.327 --> 00:40:00.170
which is, if you want,
case 2b.

00:40:00.170 --> 00:40:08.860
The external forces are 0,
the center of mass was 0;

00:40:08.860 --> 00:40:11.190
in other words,
center of mass was at rest.

00:40:18.329 --> 00:40:20.995
If you find these different
cases complicated,

00:40:20.995 --> 00:40:23.719
then I don't mind telling you
one more time.

00:40:23.719 --> 00:40:26.853
The center of mass behaves like
a single object responding to

00:40:26.853 --> 00:40:29.323
the external force.
It's clear that if the external

00:40:29.323 --> 00:40:31.139
force is non-zero,
the center of mass will

00:40:31.139 --> 00:40:33.146
accelerate.
If the external force is 0,

00:40:33.146 --> 00:40:35.200
the center of mass will not
accelerate.

00:40:35.200 --> 00:40:39.075
There are cases 1 and 2.
2a and 2b are the following:

00:40:39.075 --> 00:40:42.690
if it does not accelerate,
its velocity will not change.

00:40:42.690 --> 00:40:46.265
So then, you have the two
cases, it had a velocity,

00:40:46.265 --> 00:40:49.269
which it maintained,
or it had no velocity,

00:40:49.269 --> 00:40:52.130
in which case it does not even
move.

00:40:52.130 --> 00:40:55.592
See, if you apply F = ma
to a body and there are no

00:40:55.592 --> 00:40:58.630
forces, you cannot say the body
will be at rest.

00:40:58.630 --> 00:41:00.699
You will say the body will
maintain the velocity.

00:41:00.699 --> 00:41:03.167
So, if it had a velocity,
it'll go at the velocity,

00:41:03.167 --> 00:41:05.190
if it was at rest it'll remain
at rest;

00:41:05.190 --> 00:41:07.170
the same goes for the center of
mass.

00:41:07.170 --> 00:41:10.271
If the center of mass was
moving, it'll preserve its

00:41:10.271 --> 00:41:12.590
momentum.
That really means the sum of

00:41:12.590 --> 00:41:15.889
the momenta of the individual
pieces will be preserved.

00:41:15.889 --> 00:41:19.118
If it was at rest,
since the external force is 0,

00:41:19.118 --> 00:41:23.385
it will remain at rest.
So, I want to look at the

00:41:23.385 --> 00:41:27.502
consequence of this one.
I could've done them in either

00:41:27.502 --> 00:41:29.114
order.
I can take the case where

00:41:29.114 --> 00:41:31.372
there's no external force,
there is no motion,

00:41:31.372 --> 00:41:33.480
or I chose to do with the
opposite way,

00:41:33.480 --> 00:41:35.532
where I took the most
complicated case,

00:41:35.532 --> 00:41:38.898
where external force is not 0.
Then, I took the case where it

00:41:38.898 --> 00:41:41.739
is 0 but the center of mass was
moving to begin with,

00:41:41.739 --> 00:41:44.690
and therefore it has to keep
moving no matter what.

00:41:44.690 --> 00:41:47.239
And the simplest case is the
center of mass was at rest;

00:41:47.239 --> 00:41:50.880
then, it's not moving now and
it will never move.

00:41:50.880 --> 00:41:55.059
So, let me give an example of
where the idea comes into play.

00:41:55.059 --> 00:41:59.797
We looked at the planetary
motion of the Sun and the Earth,

00:41:59.797 --> 00:42:03.064
and I said the Earth goes
around the Sun,

00:42:03.064 --> 00:42:06.250
so let's look at it a little
later;

00:42:06.250 --> 00:42:09.593
there's the Earth and the only
force between the Earth and the

00:42:09.593 --> 00:42:11.840
Sun is the mutual force of
gravitation.

00:42:15.380 --> 00:42:19.757
Now, my question to you is,
"Is this picture of the Sun

00:42:19.757 --> 00:42:24.377
sitting here and the Earth
moving around acceptable or not

00:42:24.377 --> 00:42:27.739
in view of what I've said?"
Yes?

00:42:27.739 --> 00:42:29.994
Student: The Sun and
Earth revolve around a mutual

00:42:29.994 --> 00:42:31.338
center of gravity.
Professor Ramamurti

00:42:31.338 --> 00:42:32.340
Shankar: Yes,
that's the answer to the

00:42:32.340 --> 00:42:34.216
problem.
But what is wrong if I just say

00:42:34.216 --> 00:42:36.859
the Sun remains here and the
Earth goes in a circle,

00:42:36.859 --> 00:42:38.880
which is what we accepted last
time?

00:42:38.880 --> 00:42:41.720
Student: The momentum of
the Sun doesn't change,

00:42:41.720 --> 00:42:44.139
but it changes in the momentum
of the Earth.

00:42:44.139 --> 00:42:45.410
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: That's one way.

00:42:45.410 --> 00:42:47.808
Do you understand what he said?
He said the momentum of the Sun

00:42:47.808 --> 00:42:50.326
is not changing.
The momentum of the Earth is

00:42:50.326 --> 00:42:53.150
changing, so the total momentum
is changing.

00:42:53.150 --> 00:42:55.886
The total momentum cannot
change, so that's not

00:42:55.886 --> 00:42:58.723
acceptable.
But in terms of center of mass,

00:42:58.723 --> 00:43:00.920
you can say something else,
yes?

00:43:00.920 --> 00:43:02.530
Student: The center of
mass moves.

00:43:02.530 --> 00:43:04.428
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: It moves,

00:43:04.428 --> 00:43:06.456
maybe you can tell me,
you cannot point out from

00:43:06.456 --> 00:43:08.830
there, but tell me which way you
think it's moving.

00:43:08.830 --> 00:43:10.789
Student: In a circle.
Professor Ramamurti

00:43:10.789 --> 00:43:12.764
Shankar: Right,
in the beginning it's somewhere

00:43:12.764 --> 00:43:14.395
here.
A little later it's there,

00:43:14.395 --> 00:43:17.229
a little later it's there,
so the center of mass would do

00:43:17.229 --> 00:43:20.570
this, if the picture I gave you
last time was actually correct.

00:43:20.570 --> 00:43:24.777
So, a Sun of finite mass
staying at rest and a planet

00:43:24.777 --> 00:43:28.500
orbiting around it is simply not
acceptable,

00:43:28.500 --> 00:43:33.510
because the center of mass is
moving without external forces;

00:43:33.510 --> 00:43:35.301
that's not allowed.
Or as he said,

00:43:35.301 --> 00:43:38.149
the momentum is constantly
changing, this guy has no

00:43:38.149 --> 00:43:40.207
momentum,
that guy has the momentum that

00:43:40.207 --> 00:43:42.380
points this way now and points
that way later.

00:43:42.380 --> 00:43:45.726
But look what I've said here:
take 1 and 2 to be the Earth

00:43:45.726 --> 00:43:48.780
and the Sun, it doesn't add up
to the same number.

00:43:48.780 --> 00:43:53.289
So, we sort of know what the
answer should be.

00:43:53.289 --> 00:43:56.695
We know that the thing that
cannot move is not the Sun and

00:43:56.695 --> 00:43:59.640
it's not the Earth.
It's the center of mass;

00:43:59.640 --> 00:44:03.355
that's what cannot move.
If originally it was at rest,

00:44:03.355 --> 00:44:06.345
it'll remain at rest.
So, the center of mass,

00:44:06.345 --> 00:44:09.416
if it cannot move,
so let's start off the Sun

00:44:09.416 --> 00:44:13.604
here, start off the Earth here,
join them, the center of mass

00:44:13.604 --> 00:44:16.762
is somewhere here.
Actually, the Sun is so much

00:44:16.762 --> 00:44:19.979
more massive than the Earth,
the center of mass lies inside

00:44:19.979 --> 00:44:22.257
the Sun.
But I'm taking another Solar

00:44:22.257 --> 00:44:25.890
System where the Sun is a lot
bigger than the Earth but not as

00:44:25.890 --> 00:44:28.652
big as in our world,
so I can show the center of

00:44:28.652 --> 00:44:31.170
mass here.
That cannot move.

00:44:31.170 --> 00:44:34.016
So, what that means is,
a little later,

00:44:34.016 --> 00:44:38.510
if the planet is here and I
want to keep the center there,

00:44:38.510 --> 00:44:41.782
the Sun has to be here,
and somewhat later when the

00:44:41.782 --> 00:44:44.400
planet's there the Sun has to be
here.

00:44:44.400 --> 00:44:48.153
So, what will happen is,
the Sun will go around on a

00:44:48.153 --> 00:44:51.979
circle of smaller radius,
the planet will go around on a

00:44:51.979 --> 00:44:55.229
circle of a bigger radius,
always around the center of

00:44:55.229 --> 00:44:57.218
mass.
So, you've got this picture

00:44:57.218 --> 00:45:00.049
now, it's like a dumbbell,
asymmetric, big guy here,

00:45:00.049 --> 00:45:02.269
small guy here,
fix that and turn it.

00:45:02.269 --> 00:45:06.210
You get a trajectory for the
Sun, and you get a trajectory

00:45:06.210 --> 00:45:08.630
for the Earth on a bigger
circle;

00:45:08.630 --> 00:45:12.478
the center remains fixed.
So, if you apply loss of

00:45:12.478 --> 00:45:15.346
gravity, I've given you a
homework problem,

00:45:15.346 --> 00:45:18.349
you've got to be careful about
one thing.

00:45:18.349 --> 00:45:22.710
When you apply the Law of
Gravity, you may apply it to the

00:45:22.710 --> 00:45:25.752
Earth for example.
Then, you will say the

00:45:25.752 --> 00:45:29.603
centripetal acceleration
mv^(2) /r is the force of

00:45:29.603 --> 00:45:32.336
gravity.
When you do that calculation be

00:45:32.336 --> 00:45:34.753
careful;
v is the velocity of the

00:45:34.753 --> 00:45:37.429
planet, and when you do the
mv^(2)/r,

00:45:37.429 --> 00:45:40.067
the r you put will be
the distance to the center of

00:45:40.067 --> 00:45:44.170
mass from where you are.
That'll be the mv^(2)/r.

00:45:44.170 --> 00:45:46.405
But when you equate that to the
force of gravity,

00:45:46.405 --> 00:45:48.408
the Gm_1m
_2 over

00:45:48.408 --> 00:45:51.054
r^(2),
for that r it is the

00:45:51.054 --> 00:45:55.449
actual distance from the Earth
to the Sun that you should keep,

00:45:55.449 --> 00:45:57.888
because the force of gravity is
a function of the distance

00:45:57.888 --> 00:46:00.512
between the planets,
not between the planet and the

00:46:00.512 --> 00:46:03.198
center of mass.
The actual force on the Earth

00:46:03.198 --> 00:46:06.836
is really coming not from here
but on the other side of this

00:46:06.836 --> 00:46:08.859
where the Sun is.
But luckily,

00:46:08.859 --> 00:46:11.884
at every instant,
the Sun is constantly pulling

00:46:11.884 --> 00:46:14.450
it towards the center of the
circle.

00:46:14.450 --> 00:46:17.956
It's a very clever solution.
The planet moves around a

00:46:17.956 --> 00:46:20.282
circle.
It has an acceleration towards

00:46:20.282 --> 00:46:23.340
the center, and somebody's
providing that force.

00:46:23.340 --> 00:46:26.179
ut that somebody is not at the
center but always on the other

00:46:26.179 --> 00:46:28.309
side of the line joining you to
the center,

00:46:28.309 --> 00:46:31.219
so you still experience a force
towards the center.

00:46:31.219 --> 00:46:34.480
Under the action of that force,
you can show it'll have a

00:46:34.480 --> 00:46:38.149
circular orbit and you can take
some time in calculating now the

00:46:38.149 --> 00:46:41.409
relation between time period and
radius and whatnot.

00:46:41.409 --> 00:46:42.860
So, this is called a two-body
problem.

00:46:46.590 --> 00:46:49.222
So, this is one example where
you realize, "Hey,

00:46:49.222 --> 00:46:51.070
center of mass,
if I follow it,

00:46:51.070 --> 00:46:54.197
it cannot be moving and
therefore the actual motion of

00:46:54.197 --> 00:46:56.969
planets is more complicated than
we thought."

00:46:56.969 --> 00:47:02.033
Okay, then, there is a whole
slew of problems one can do,

00:47:02.033 --> 00:47:05.739
where the center of mass is not
moving.

00:47:05.739 --> 00:47:07.400
So, I'll just give you a couple
of examples;

00:47:07.400 --> 00:47:09.930
then, I will stop,
but I won't do the numbers.

00:47:09.930 --> 00:47:15.259
Here is one example.
That is a carriage that

00:47:15.259 --> 00:47:21.343
contains a horse,
and the horse is on this far

00:47:21.343 --> 00:47:23.996
end.
And as they tell us to do,

00:47:23.996 --> 00:47:27.344
we won't draw the horse,
we'll just say it's a point

00:47:27.344 --> 00:47:30.440
mass m,
and the railway carriage is a

00:47:30.440 --> 00:47:34.334
big mass, capital M,
and let's say the left hand of

00:47:34.334 --> 00:47:39.369
the railway carriage is here.
Now, you cannot see the horse,

00:47:39.369 --> 00:47:41.760
okay?
The horse is inside;

00:47:41.760 --> 00:47:45.006
the horse decides to--;now,
he said, "I'm tired of sitting

00:47:45.006 --> 00:47:48.309
on this side of this room,
I'm going to the other side."

00:47:48.309 --> 00:47:50.500
The horse goes to the other
side.

00:47:50.500 --> 00:47:53.041
First of all,
you will know something's going

00:47:53.041 --> 00:47:56.103
on without looking in,
because when the horse moves to

00:47:56.103 --> 00:47:59.050
the left the carriage has to
move to the right.

00:47:59.050 --> 00:48:02.239
First, convince yourself the
carriage has to move somewhere

00:48:02.239 --> 00:48:05.650
because originally the center of
mass between these two objects

00:48:05.650 --> 00:48:08.730
-- that one and that one -- is
something in between,

00:48:08.730 --> 00:48:11.991
somewhere here.
If the horse came to that side,

00:48:11.991 --> 00:48:14.912
the center of mass is now the
average of those two,

00:48:14.912 --> 00:48:18.313
which is somewhere over there;
the center of mass has moved

00:48:18.313 --> 00:48:21.260
and that's not allowed,
the center of mass cannot move.

00:48:21.260 --> 00:48:24.243
So, if the center of mass is
originally on that line,

00:48:24.243 --> 00:48:27.798
it has to remain in that line.
So, what will happen in the end

00:48:27.798 --> 00:48:31.067
is that the horse will come
here, the center of the carriage

00:48:31.067 --> 00:48:33.338
will be there,
but the center of mass will

00:48:33.338 --> 00:48:36.569
come out the same way.
So, a typical problem,

00:48:36.569 --> 00:48:42.010
you guys will be expected to
solve, will look like this.

00:48:42.010 --> 00:48:46.255
Given all these masses and
given the length of the

00:48:46.255 --> 00:48:50.500
carriage, find out how much the
carriage moves.

00:48:50.500 --> 00:48:53.970
Do you think you can do that?
Give some numbers and plug in

00:48:53.970 --> 00:48:55.725
the things.
For example,

00:48:55.725 --> 00:48:59.849
this guy is at a distance
L/2 of this;

00:48:59.849 --> 00:49:01.860
the horse is at a distance
L.

00:49:01.860 --> 00:49:03.739
Make this your origin of
coordinates.

00:49:03.739 --> 00:49:06.777
Take the weighted average of
those two, and get the x

00:49:06.777 --> 00:49:08.579
coordinate of the center of
mass.

00:49:08.579 --> 00:49:10.921
You don't have to worry about
the y because there's

00:49:10.921 --> 00:49:12.400
nothing happening in the
y.

00:49:12.400 --> 00:49:15.410
So, the x coordinate of
that and that'll be somewhere in

00:49:15.410 --> 00:49:16.836
here.
At the end of the day,

00:49:16.836 --> 00:49:19.406
let us say it has moved an
unknown distance d,

00:49:19.406 --> 00:49:21.579
which is what you're trying to
calculate.

00:49:21.579 --> 00:49:24.349
Then, compute the center of
mass.

00:49:24.349 --> 00:49:27.210
When you do that,
remember that the center of the

00:49:27.210 --> 00:49:30.369
carriage is L/2 +
d from this origin.

00:49:30.369 --> 00:49:32.989
The horse is at the distance
d from the origin.

00:49:32.989 --> 00:49:36.296
Equate the center as a mass and
you will get an equation that

00:49:36.296 --> 00:49:38.280
the only unknown will be
d,

00:49:38.280 --> 00:49:43.245
and you solve for a d
and it'll tell you how much it

00:49:43.245 --> 00:49:45.789
moves.
Anybody have a question about

00:49:45.789 --> 00:49:49.609
how you attack this problem?
Find the center of mass before,

00:49:49.609 --> 00:49:53.211
find the center of mass after,
equate them and that linear

00:49:53.211 --> 00:49:56.890
equation will have one unknown,
which is the d by which

00:49:56.890 --> 00:49:59.390
the carriage has moved and you
can solve for it.

00:49:59.390 --> 00:50:02.840
Okay, here's another problem.

00:50:06.760 --> 00:50:10.380
Here is a shore,
and here is a boat;

00:50:10.380 --> 00:50:17.431
maybe I'll show the boat like a
boat, here it is,

00:50:17.431 --> 00:50:22.810
okay that's the boat.
Now, you are here.

00:50:26.829 --> 00:50:30.441
So, the boat has a certain
mass, which we can pretend is

00:50:30.441 --> 00:50:33.481
concentrated there.
You have a little mass

00:50:33.481 --> 00:50:36.803
m, and the boat is at a
distance, say,

00:50:36.803 --> 00:50:39.093
d,
from the shore,

00:50:39.093 --> 00:50:44.166
and you are at a certain
distance x from the edge

00:50:44.166 --> 00:50:48.519
of the boat,
and you want to get out, okay.

00:50:48.519 --> 00:50:51.789
You want to go to shore,
so what do you do?

00:50:51.789 --> 00:50:55.759
So, if you're Superman or
Superwoman you just take off and

00:50:55.759 --> 00:50:59.160
you land where you want.
But suppose you have limited

00:50:59.160 --> 00:51:02.114
jumping capabilities.
It is very natural that you

00:51:02.114 --> 00:51:05.840
want to come as far to the left
as possible and then jump.

00:51:05.840 --> 00:51:08.591
Suppose it is true that
d, which is,

00:51:08.591 --> 00:51:11.801
say, three meters,
is the maximum you can possibly

00:51:11.801 --> 00:51:14.880
jump, whereas you cannot jump
d + x.

00:51:14.880 --> 00:51:16.643
So, you say,
"Let me go to the end and I'm

00:51:16.643 --> 00:51:18.750
safe because I can jump the
distance d."

00:51:18.750 --> 00:51:24.265
And again, we know that's not
going to work because when you

00:51:24.265 --> 00:51:28.636
move--Look it's very simple.
If you move and nobody else

00:51:28.636 --> 00:51:31.943
moves we've got a problem,
because if you found the center

00:51:31.943 --> 00:51:34.090
of mass with one location for
you,

00:51:34.090 --> 00:51:36.462
and you change your location
and nothing else changes,

00:51:36.462 --> 00:51:38.789
center of mass will change and
that's not allowed.

00:51:38.789 --> 00:51:42.230
Here, I'm assuming there are no
horizontal forces.

00:51:42.230 --> 00:51:44.106
In real life,
the water will exert a

00:51:44.106 --> 00:51:46.412
horizontal force,
but that's ignored in this

00:51:46.412 --> 00:51:48.769
calculation.
There are no horizontal forces.

00:51:48.769 --> 00:51:50.750
If you move,
everything else has to move.

00:51:50.750 --> 00:51:54.143
So, what'll happen is that,
when you move,

00:51:54.143 --> 00:51:58.943
the boat will have moved from
there maybe somewhere over to

00:51:58.943 --> 00:52:02.559
the right like this.
You are certainly at the edge

00:52:02.559 --> 00:52:05.819
of the boat, but the boat has
moved a little extra distance

00:52:05.819 --> 00:52:08.630
δ, and you have to find
that δ.

00:52:08.630 --> 00:52:13.784
You find it by the same trick.
You find the center of mass of

00:52:13.784 --> 00:52:17.635
you and the boat,
preferably with this as the

00:52:17.635 --> 00:52:20.115
origin.
You can use any origin you want

00:52:20.115 --> 00:52:22.496
for center of mass,
it's not going and it's not

00:52:22.496 --> 00:52:25.608
going according to anybody,
but it's convenient to pick the

00:52:25.608 --> 00:52:28.122
shore as your origin,
find the weighted sum of your

00:52:28.122 --> 00:52:31.138
location and your mass,
the boat's location and boat's

00:52:31.138 --> 00:52:32.707
mass.
At the end of the day,

00:52:32.707 --> 00:52:35.943
put yourself on the left hand
of the boat, and let's say it

00:52:35.943 --> 00:52:39.479
has moved a distance δ,
so the real distance now is

00:52:39.479 --> 00:52:42.869
d + δ.
That's where you are.

00:52:42.869 --> 00:52:45.860
That plus L/2 is where
the center of the boat is.

00:52:45.860 --> 00:52:48.728
Now, find the new center of
mass and equate them and you

00:52:48.728 --> 00:52:51.179
will find how much the boat
would have moved,

00:52:51.179 --> 00:52:55.450
and that means you have to jump
a distance d + δ.

00:52:55.450 --> 00:53:00.795
Everybody follow that?
That's another example where

00:53:00.795 --> 00:53:04.195
the center of mass doesn't move.
Now, let's ask what happens

00:53:04.195 --> 00:53:07.160
next.
So, you leap in the air, okay?

00:53:07.160 --> 00:53:12.434
Now you're airborne.
What do you think is happening

00:53:12.434 --> 00:53:15.940
when you're airborne?
Yes?

00:53:15.940 --> 00:53:17.690
Go ahead!
What's happening?

00:53:17.690 --> 00:53:20.630
Student: The boat will
move the other way.

00:53:20.630 --> 00:53:21.980
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: It'll be moving,

00:53:21.980 --> 00:53:22.960
and why do you say it'll be
moving?

00:53:22.960 --> 00:53:24.859
Student: Why?
Professor Ramamurti

00:53:24.859 --> 00:53:26.122
Shankar: Yeah.
Student: Because the

00:53:26.122 --> 00:53:27.539
center of mass still won't be
the same thing.

00:53:27.539 --> 00:53:28.186
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Right,

00:53:28.186 --> 00:53:29.654
there's one way to say that.
The center of mass cannot move,

00:53:29.654 --> 00:53:31.321
so if you move to the left,
the boat will move to the

00:53:31.321 --> 00:53:32.914
right.
What's the equivalent way to

00:53:32.914 --> 00:53:34.389
say that?
Yes?

00:53:34.389 --> 00:53:35.920
Student: The momentum
can't change.

00:53:35.920 --> 00:53:36.681
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Right,

00:53:36.681 --> 00:53:38.900
the momentum cannot change.
Originally, the momentum was 0,

00:53:38.900 --> 00:53:41.340
nobody was moving,
but suddenly you're moving,

00:53:41.340 --> 00:53:43.400
the boat has to move the other
way.

00:53:43.400 --> 00:53:46.446
Of course, it doesn't move with
the same velocity,

00:53:46.446 --> 00:53:49.909
or the same speed;
it moves with the same momentum.

00:53:49.909 --> 00:53:53.051
So, the big M of the
boat times the small v of

00:53:53.051 --> 00:53:55.927
the boat, will equal your small
m times your big

00:53:55.927 --> 00:53:57.484
V.
In other words,

00:53:57.484 --> 00:54:00.885
you, unless you move with a big
speed, the boat moves with a

00:54:00.885 --> 00:54:03.182
small speed;
then, these two numbers in

00:54:03.182 --> 00:54:06.268
magnitude will be equal.
So, if you're going on one of

00:54:06.268 --> 00:54:08.800
the big cruise ships,
you jump on the shore,

00:54:08.800 --> 00:54:12.039
you're not going to notice the
movement of the ship,

00:54:12.039 --> 00:54:14.640
but it technically speaking
does move the other way.

00:54:14.640 --> 00:54:19.279
Okay, you're airborne, okay.
Then, a few seconds later you

00:54:19.279 --> 00:54:22.190
collapse on the shore;
you're right there.

00:54:22.190 --> 00:54:23.790
Now, what's happening to the
boat?

00:54:23.790 --> 00:54:28.219
Is it going to stop now?
Your momentum is 0, yes?

00:54:28.219 --> 00:54:32.401
Student: But you've been
stopped by the force of the

00:54:32.401 --> 00:54:33.660
ground.
Professor Ramamurti

00:54:33.660 --> 00:54:35.530
Shankar: Yes.
Everybody agree?

00:54:35.530 --> 00:54:38.187
I will repeat that answer,
but you should all have figured

00:54:38.187 --> 00:54:40.539
this out.
The boat will not stop just

00:54:40.539 --> 00:54:43.324
because you hit the shore.
The boat will keep moving

00:54:43.324 --> 00:54:44.760
because there's no force on the
boat;

00:54:44.760 --> 00:54:46.801
it's going to keep moving.
The question is,

00:54:46.801 --> 00:54:49.515
"How come I suddenly have
momentum in my system when I had

00:54:49.515 --> 00:54:52.058
no momentum before?"
It's because the F

00:54:52.058 --> 00:54:55.494
external has now come into play.
Previously, it was just you and

00:54:55.494 --> 00:54:58.150
the boat and you couldn't change
your total momentum.

00:54:58.150 --> 00:55:00.598
But the ground is now pushing
you, and it's obviously pushing

00:55:00.598 --> 00:55:03.006
you to the right because you
were flying to the left and you

00:55:03.006 --> 00:55:05.003
were stopped.
So, your combined system,

00:55:05.003 --> 00:55:07.402
you and the boat,
have a rightward force acting

00:55:07.402 --> 00:55:09.280
for the time it took to stop
you;

00:55:09.280 --> 00:55:12.989
it's that momentum that's
carried by the boat.

00:55:12.989 --> 00:55:16.158
A better way to say this is,
you and the boat exchange

00:55:16.158 --> 00:55:18.670
momenta, you push the boat to
the right,

00:55:18.670 --> 00:55:20.896
you move to the left,
and your momentum is killed by

00:55:20.896 --> 00:55:23.398
the shore.
The boat, no reason to change,

00:55:23.398 --> 00:55:26.367
and keeps going.
So, can you calculate how fast

00:55:26.367 --> 00:55:27.600
the boat is moving?

00:55:31.050 --> 00:55:33.281
Can anybody tell me how to
calculate how fast the boat is

00:55:33.281 --> 00:55:33.640
moving?

00:55:37.750 --> 00:55:42.791
Yes?
Student: [inaudible]

00:55:42.791 --> 00:55:45.951
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: But I'm on the

00:55:45.951 --> 00:55:47.710
shore now.
I've fallen on the shore.

00:55:47.710 --> 00:55:49.269
I'm asking how fast the boat is
moving.

00:55:49.269 --> 00:55:53.003
Student: The boat is
moving as fast as [inaudible]

00:55:53.003 --> 00:55:55.736
Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Right,

00:55:55.736 --> 00:55:58.269
I think he's got the right
answer.

00:55:58.269 --> 00:56:01.328
If I only told you that I
jumped and landed on the shore,

00:56:01.328 --> 00:56:04.550
that's not enough to predict
how fast the boat is moving.

00:56:04.550 --> 00:56:07.915
But if I told you my velocity
when I was airborne,

00:56:07.915 --> 00:56:11.555
then of course I know my
momentum and you can find the

00:56:11.555 --> 00:56:16.019
boat momentum and that's the
velocity it will retain forever.

00:56:16.019 --> 00:56:18.309
So, you need more information
than simply saying,

00:56:18.309 --> 00:56:21.344
"I jumped to the shore."
It depends with what velocity I

00:56:21.344 --> 00:56:23.659
left the boat and landed on the
ground.

00:56:23.659 --> 00:56:26.522
If I leap really hard,
the boat will go really fast

00:56:26.522 --> 00:56:30.738
the opposite way.
Okay, that's the end of this

00:56:30.738 --> 00:56:34.650
family of center of mass
problems.

00:56:34.650 --> 00:56:39.530
So, I'm going to another class
of problems.

00:56:42.579 --> 00:56:45.913
This involves a rocket,
and it's going to derive the

00:56:45.913 --> 00:56:48.227
rocket equation.
A rocket is something everybody

00:56:48.227 --> 00:56:50.539
understands but it's a little
more complicated than you think.

00:56:50.539 --> 00:56:53.279
Everyone knows you blow up a
balloon, you let it go,

00:56:53.279 --> 00:56:56.372
the balloon goes one way,
the air goes the other way,

00:56:56.372 --> 00:56:59.900
action and reaction are equal,
even lay people know that.

00:56:59.900 --> 00:57:04.177
Or, if you stand on a frozen
lake and you take a gun and you

00:57:04.177 --> 00:57:07.055
fire something,
but then the bullet goes one

00:57:07.055 --> 00:57:10.698
way and you go the opposite way,
again, because of conservation

00:57:10.698 --> 00:57:13.061
of momentum.
The rocket is a little more

00:57:13.061 --> 00:57:16.079
subtle and I just want to
mention a few aspects of it.

00:57:16.079 --> 00:57:18.440
I don't want to go into the
rocket problem in any detail.

00:57:18.440 --> 00:57:21.449
It's good for you to know how
these things are done.

00:57:21.449 --> 00:57:25.479
Here's a rocket whose mass at
this instant is M,

00:57:25.479 --> 00:57:28.389
whose velocity is v
right now.

00:57:28.389 --> 00:57:33.289
What rockets do is they emit
gasses, and the gasses have a

00:57:33.289 --> 00:57:36.760
certain exhaust velocity.
That velocity is called

00:57:36.760 --> 00:57:38.733
v_0.
In magnitude,

00:57:38.733 --> 00:57:42.699
it's pointing away from the
rocket, and it has a fixed value

00:57:42.699 --> 00:57:46.329
relative to the rocket,
not relative to the ground.

00:57:46.329 --> 00:57:48.984
If you are riding with the
rocket and you look at the fumes

00:57:48.984 --> 00:57:51.272
coming out of the back,
they will be leaving you at

00:57:51.272 --> 00:57:55.239
that speed v_0.
A short time later--What

00:57:55.239 --> 00:58:00.556
happens a short time later,
the rocket has a mass M -

00:58:00.556 --> 00:58:06.743
δ because it's lost some of
its own body mass in the form of

00:58:06.743 --> 00:58:09.908
exhaust fumes.
The exhaust fumes,

00:58:09.908 --> 00:58:14.485
I'm just showing them as a blob
here, and the rocket's velocity

00:58:14.485 --> 00:58:17.659
now is not v,
but v + Δv.

00:58:17.659 --> 00:58:20.719
And what's the velocity of the
fumes?

00:58:20.719 --> 00:58:22.329
Here's where you've got to be
careful.

00:58:22.329 --> 00:58:24.483
If your velocity was v
at that instant,

00:58:24.483 --> 00:58:27.258
the velocity of the rocket
fume, with respect to the ground

00:58:27.258 --> 00:58:30.558
is v - v_0;
that's the part you've got to

00:58:30.558 --> 00:58:31.290
understand.

00:58:34.730 --> 00:58:37.280
The rocket has a smaller mass
and bigger velocity;

00:58:37.280 --> 00:58:41.048
everyone understands that.
But what's the momentum of the

00:58:41.048 --> 00:58:45.130
gas leaving the rocket if the
mass is δ?

00:58:45.130 --> 00:58:48.594
But what is its velocity?
Its velocity with respect to

00:58:48.594 --> 00:58:52.159
the rocket is pointing to the
left of v_0,

00:58:52.159 --> 00:58:55.039
but the rocket itself is going
to the right at speed v.

00:58:55.039 --> 00:58:56.771
So, the speed as seen from the
ground will be v -

00:58:56.771 --> 00:58:57.450
v_0.

00:59:01.710 --> 00:59:13.069
So, the Law of Conservation of
Momentum will say Mv = (M -

00:59:13.069 --> 00:59:21.400
δ) (v + Δv) + δ(v -
v_0).

00:59:21.400 --> 00:59:24.369
This is, the momentum before
and the momentum after are

00:59:24.369 --> 00:59:27.412
equal.
So, you open out this bracket

00:59:27.412 --> 00:59:32.348
you get -- sorry my letters
better be uniform -- this is

00:59:32.348 --> 00:59:38.383
Mv, then -vδ.
I don't want to call it

00:59:38.383 --> 00:59:47.012
δv, I want to call it
vδ + MΔv - (δ) (Δv ) + δv -

00:59:47.012 --> 00:59:50.760
v_0δ.
I want to call it vδ.

00:59:50.760 --> 00:59:53.445
The reason I want to put the
δ on the right is you

00:59:53.445 --> 00:59:55.729
may get confused.
δ usually stands for

00:59:55.729 --> 00:59:58.309
the change of something,
so that's not what I mean.

00:59:58.309 --> 01:00:02.579
So, you cancel this Mv
and you cancel this Mv.

01:00:02.579 --> 01:00:07.829
You cancel this vδ and
that vδ.

01:00:07.829 --> 01:00:11.141
This one you ignore because
it's the product of two

01:00:11.141 --> 01:00:14.188
infinitesimals,
one is the amount of gas in the

01:00:14.188 --> 01:00:17.345
small time δt,
the other is infinitesimal

01:00:17.345 --> 01:00:20.333
change in velocity;
we keep things which are linear

01:00:20.333 --> 01:00:24.156
in this.
Then, you get the result

01:00:24.156 --> 01:00:30.300
MΔv = v_0
times δ.

01:00:34.239 --> 01:00:39.932
So, I'm going to write it as
Δv/v_0 = δ

01:00:39.932 --> 01:00:41.530
over M.

01:00:46.460 --> 01:00:49.049
This is the relation between
the change in the velocity of

01:00:49.049 --> 01:00:51.398
the rocket;
the velocity of the exhaust

01:00:51.398 --> 01:00:55.044
gases seen by the rocket,
the amount emitted in the small

01:00:55.044 --> 01:00:57.909
time divided by the mass at that
instant.

01:00:57.909 --> 01:01:02.555
But in the sense of calculus,
what is the change [dM]

01:01:02.555 --> 01:01:07.054
in the mass of the rocket?
If M is the mass of the

01:01:07.054 --> 01:01:11.415
rocket, what would you call this
a change, the mass of the

01:01:11.415 --> 01:01:16.300
rocket, in this short time?
Yep?

01:01:16.300 --> 01:01:17.977
Student: [inaudible]
Professor Ramamurti

01:01:17.977 --> 01:01:19.585
Shankar: No,
no, no, in terms of the symbols

01:01:19.585 --> 01:01:21.400
here what's the change in the
mass of the rocket?

01:01:21.400 --> 01:01:22.278
Student: δ
Professor Ramamurti

01:01:22.278 --> 01:01:24.134
Shankar: It's δ,
but it's really speaking

01:01:24.134 --> 01:01:27.478
-δ. You could keep track
of the sign, the change in the

01:01:27.478 --> 01:01:30.862
variable is really negative,
and delta here stands for a

01:01:30.862 --> 01:01:34.707
positive number.
So, if you remember that,

01:01:34.707 --> 01:01:40.390
you'll write this -dM/M.
Now, the rest is simple

01:01:40.390 --> 01:01:42.922
mathematics.
I don't want to do this,

01:01:42.922 --> 01:01:46.119
but if you integrate this side
and you integrate that side,

01:01:46.119 --> 01:01:48.489
and you know dM/M is a
logarithm;

01:01:48.489 --> 01:01:55.016
you will find the result that
the v at any time is

01:01:55.016 --> 01:02:01.427
v final = v
initial plus--or maybe I might

01:02:01.427 --> 01:02:08.228
as well do this integral here.
This integral will be v

01:02:08.228 --> 01:02:12.958
final - v initial over
v_0,

01:02:12.958 --> 01:02:18.539
will be the log of M
initial over M final.

01:02:18.539 --> 01:02:22.589
So, you will find final is
v initial +

01:02:22.589 --> 01:02:27.559
v_0 log
M initial over M

01:02:27.559 --> 01:02:29.869
final.
I'm doing it rather fast

01:02:29.869 --> 01:02:33.402
because I'm not that interested
in following this equation any

01:02:33.402 --> 01:02:35.286
further.
It's not a key equation like

01:02:35.286 --> 01:02:36.800
what I've been talking about
now.

01:02:41.639 --> 01:02:44.068
So, this is just to show you
how we can apply the Law of

01:02:44.068 --> 01:02:46.477
Conservation of Momentum.
I'm not going to hold you

01:02:46.477 --> 01:02:49.010
responsible in any great detail
for the derivation,

01:02:49.010 --> 01:02:51.822
but that is a formula that
tells you the velocity of the

01:02:51.822 --> 01:02:54.472
rocket at any instant,
if you knew the mass at that

01:02:54.472 --> 01:02:54.930
instant.

01:03:00.130 --> 01:03:03.417
The rocket will pick up speed
and its mass will keep going

01:03:03.417 --> 01:03:06.820
down, and the log of the mass
before to the mass after times

01:03:06.820 --> 01:03:10.050
v_0 is the
change in the velocity of the

01:03:10.050 --> 01:03:12.925
rocket.
Okay, so I have to give you

01:03:12.925 --> 01:03:16.940
some more ammunition to do your
homework problems;

01:03:16.940 --> 01:03:19.469
so, I'm going to discuss the
last and final topic,

01:03:19.469 --> 01:03:21.380
which is the subject of
collisions.

01:03:21.380 --> 01:03:26.748
So, we're going to take the
collision of two bodies,

01:03:26.748 --> 01:03:30.476
one body, another body,
m_1v

01:03:30.476 --> 01:03:32.668
_1,
m_2v

01:03:32.668 --> 01:03:34.860
_2,
they collide.

01:03:34.860 --> 01:03:38.087
At the end of the day,
you can have the same two

01:03:38.087 --> 01:03:41.794
bodies moving at some velocities
v_1',

01:03:41.794 --> 01:03:45.355
v_2'.
Our goal is to find the final

01:03:45.355 --> 01:03:47.850
velocities;
that's a goal of physics.

01:03:47.850 --> 01:03:50.778
I tell you what's happening now.
I'm asking you what's happening

01:03:50.778 --> 01:03:52.825
later.
So here, there are two

01:03:52.825 --> 01:03:56.666
conditions you need because
you're trying to find two

01:03:56.666 --> 01:03:58.993
unknowns, right?
We want two unknowns,

01:03:58.993 --> 01:04:01.706
I need two equations.
One equation always true,

01:04:01.706 --> 01:04:04.500
so let me write that down,
always true.

01:04:07.920 --> 01:04:13.857
Always true is the condition
that the momentum before is the

01:04:13.857 --> 01:04:18.385
momentum after,
m_1v_1'

01:04:18.385 --> 01:04:22.309
+ m_2v&lt;s
ub&gt;2'.

01:04:22.309 --> 01:04:26.222
You need a second equation to
solve for the two unknowns,

01:04:26.222 --> 01:04:30.344
and that's where there are two
extreme cases for which I can

01:04:30.344 --> 01:04:37.638
give you the second equation,
the one extreme case is called

01:04:37.638 --> 01:04:41.862
"Totally inelastic."
In a totally inelastic

01:04:41.862 --> 01:04:43.260
collision, the two masses stick
together.

01:04:43.260 --> 01:04:45.288
That means
v_1' and

01:04:45.288 --> 01:04:47.721
v_2' are not
two unknowns,

01:04:47.721 --> 01:04:49.750
but a single unknown v'.

01:04:54.280 --> 01:04:56.347
Then, it's very easy to solve
for the momentum,

01:04:56.347 --> 01:04:58.550
because they stick together and
move as a unit.

01:04:58.550 --> 01:05:04.265
So, you can write here that is
equal to (m_1 +

01:05:04.265 --> 01:05:08.214
m_2) v',
so you get v ‘=

01:05:08.214 --> 01:05:12.096
(m_1v_1 +
m_2v_2

01:05:12.096 --> 01:05:15.820
)/(m_1 +
m_2).

01:05:19.420 --> 01:05:22.037
That's a simple case:
two things hit,

01:05:22.037 --> 01:05:25.309
stick together,
and move at a common speed.

01:05:25.309 --> 01:05:28.394
The common speed should be such
that the total momentum agrees

01:05:28.394 --> 01:05:31.380
with what you had before.
That's called "total Inelastic."

01:05:31.380 --> 01:05:33.740
The other category is called
"totally elastic."

01:05:37.849 --> 01:05:40.783
In a totally elastic collision,
the kinetic energy is

01:05:40.783 --> 01:05:41.460
conserved.

01:05:46.679 --> 01:05:51.676
That you can write as the
following relation involving

01:05:51.676 --> 01:05:53.750
quadratic things,
½

01:05:53.750 --> 01:05:56.955
m_1v_1^(2) +
½

01:05:56.955 --> 01:06:00.160
m_2v_2^(2) =
½

01:06:00.160 --> 01:06:05.439
m_1v_1^('2)
+ ½ m_2v_2

01:06:05.439 --> 01:06:08.873
^('2).
You can, it turns out,

01:06:08.873 --> 01:06:11.152
juggle this equation and that
equation and solve for

01:06:11.152 --> 01:06:13.700
v_1^(') and
v_2^(').

01:06:18.989 --> 01:06:20.420
Well, I'll tell you what the
answer is.

01:06:20.420 --> 01:06:22.179
I don't expect you to keep
solving it.

01:06:22.179 --> 01:06:25.529
The answer is that
v_1^(') =

01:06:25.529 --> 01:06:29.465
(m_1 -
m_2)/(m_1 +

01:06:29.465 --> 01:06:34.574
m_2)v_1 + (2
m_2/m_1 +

01:06:34.574 --> 01:06:37.840
m_2)v&lt;
sub&gt;2.

01:06:37.840 --> 01:06:39.804
These are no great secrets;
you'll find them in any

01:06:39.804 --> 01:06:41.636
textbook.
If you cannot follow my

01:06:41.636 --> 01:06:45.022
handwriting or you're running
out of time, just what you

01:06:45.022 --> 01:06:48.778
should be understanding now is
that there are formulae for the

01:06:48.778 --> 01:06:52.350
final velocity when the
collision is totally elastic,

01:06:52.350 --> 01:06:55.399
or totally inelastic.
If they're totally inelastic,

01:06:55.399 --> 01:06:58.070
it's what I wrote there,
v^(') is something.

01:06:58.070 --> 01:07:01.659
The totally elastic you have a
formula like this one.

01:07:01.659 --> 01:07:04.010
So, here you just replace
everywhere;

01:07:04.010 --> 01:07:09.986
you saw an m_1
you put an m_2,

01:07:09.986 --> 01:07:14.159
2m_1 over
m_1 +

01:07:14.159 --> 01:07:18.524
m_2v_1.
Don't waste too much time

01:07:18.524 --> 01:07:20.121
writing this.
I think you can go home and

01:07:20.121 --> 01:07:22.039
fill in the blanks;
it's in all the books.

01:07:22.039 --> 01:07:24.851
What you carry in your head is
there's enough data to solve

01:07:24.851 --> 01:07:27.130
this, because I will tell you
the two bodies,

01:07:27.130 --> 01:07:29.121
I'll tell you their masses,
I'll tell you the initial

01:07:29.121 --> 01:07:31.161
velocities;
so plug in the numbers you get

01:07:31.161 --> 01:07:33.642
the final velocity.
So, remember this,

01:07:33.642 --> 01:07:38.159
elastic, inelastic collision,
this is in one dimension.

01:07:38.159 --> 01:07:42.251
Now, I'll give you a typical
problem where you have to be

01:07:42.251 --> 01:07:46.489
very careful in using the Law of
Conservation of Energy.

01:07:46.489 --> 01:07:49.620
You cannot use the Law of
Conservation of Energy in an

01:07:49.620 --> 01:07:52.755
inelastic collision.
In fact, I ask you to check if

01:07:52.755 --> 01:07:55.813
two bodies--Take two bodies
identical with opposite

01:07:55.813 --> 01:07:58.679
velocities;
the total momentum is 0.

01:07:58.679 --> 01:08:00.969
They slam, they sit together as
a lump.

01:08:00.969 --> 01:08:04.030
They've got no kinetic energy
in the end.

01:08:04.030 --> 01:08:06.900
In the beginning,
they both had kinetic energy.

01:08:06.900 --> 01:08:10.382
So, kinetic energy is not
conserved in a totally inelastic

01:08:10.382 --> 01:08:13.010
collision, in an elastic
collision it is.

01:08:13.010 --> 01:08:16.086
So, here is an example that
tells you how to do this

01:08:16.086 --> 01:08:19.652
carefully.
So, this is called a Ballistic

01:08:19.652 --> 01:08:22.198
Pendulum.
So, if you have a pistol -- you

01:08:22.198 --> 01:08:24.984
manufactured a pistol -- the
bullet's coming out of the

01:08:24.984 --> 01:08:27.467
pistol at a certain speed,
and you want to tell the

01:08:27.467 --> 01:08:29.840
customer what the speed is.
How do you find it?

01:08:29.840 --> 01:08:33.370
Well, nowadays we can measure
these things phenomenally well

01:08:33.370 --> 01:08:36.421
with all kinds of fancy
techniques, down to 10^(-10)

01:08:36.421 --> 01:08:37.950
seconds.
In the old days,

01:08:37.950 --> 01:08:41.399
this is the trick people had.
You go and hang a chunk of wood

01:08:41.399 --> 01:08:45.542
from the ceiling.
Then, you fire the bullet with

01:08:45.542 --> 01:08:51.890
some speed v_0
and you know its mass exactly.

01:08:51.890 --> 01:08:55.770
The bullet comes,
rams into this chunk.

01:08:55.770 --> 01:08:59.119
I cannot draw one more picture,
so you guys imagine now.

01:08:59.119 --> 01:09:02.594
The bullet is embedded in this,
and I think you also know

01:09:02.594 --> 01:09:06.131
intuitively the minute it's
embedded, the whole thing sets

01:09:06.131 --> 01:09:08.503
in motion.
Now, you could put this on a

01:09:08.503 --> 01:09:09.789
table.
Forget all the rope.

01:09:09.789 --> 01:09:12.355
If you can find the speed of
the entire combination,

01:09:12.355 --> 01:09:15.322
then by using Conservation of
Momentum, you can find out the

01:09:15.322 --> 01:09:18.180
speed of the bullet.
But that's hard to measure;

01:09:18.180 --> 01:09:19.980
people have a much cleverer
idea.

01:09:19.980 --> 01:09:22.880
You should ram into this thing.
This is like a pendulum.

01:09:22.880 --> 01:09:26.937
So, the pendulum rises up now
to a certain maximum height that

01:09:26.937 --> 01:09:30.603
you can easily measure.
And from that maximum height

01:09:30.603 --> 01:09:33.680
you can calculate the speed of
the bullet.

01:09:33.680 --> 01:09:37.476
So, I'm going to conclude by
telling you what equations

01:09:37.476 --> 01:09:40.430
you're allowed to use in the two
stages;

01:09:40.430 --> 01:09:42.699
so pay attention and then we're
done.

01:09:42.699 --> 01:09:45.548
In the first collision,
when the bullet rammed into

01:09:45.548 --> 01:09:48.909
this block, you cannot use Law
of Conservation of Energy.

01:09:48.909 --> 01:09:51.434
In other words,
you might be naive and say,

01:09:51.434 --> 01:09:54.619
"Look, I don't care about what
happened in between;

01:09:54.619 --> 01:09:57.559
finally, I've got a certain
energy, M + m times

01:09:57.559 --> 01:10:00.387
g times h,
that's my potential energy,

01:10:00.387 --> 01:10:02.917
not kinetic."
Initially, I had ½

01:10:02.917 --> 01:10:06.777
m_0^(2).
I equate these two guys and I

01:10:06.777 --> 01:10:09.090
found v_0;
that would be wrong.

01:10:09.090 --> 01:10:12.523
That's wrong because you cannot
use the Law of Conservation of

01:10:12.523 --> 01:10:15.731
Energy in this process when I
tell you that it's a totally

01:10:15.731 --> 01:10:17.869
inelastic collision in the
middle.

01:10:17.869 --> 01:10:20.357
Because, what'll happen is,
some energy will go into

01:10:20.357 --> 01:10:22.869
heating up the block;
it might even catch fire if the

01:10:22.869 --> 01:10:25.925
bullet's going too fast.
But you can use the Law of

01:10:25.925 --> 01:10:30.539
Conservation of Momentum all the
time in the first collision to

01:10:30.539 --> 01:10:34.930
deduce that M + m times
some intermediate velocity is

01:10:34.930 --> 01:10:38.869
the incoming momentum.
You understand that?

01:10:38.869 --> 01:10:41.916
From that, you can find the
velocity v with which

01:10:41.916 --> 01:10:44.021
this composite thing,
block and bullet,

01:10:44.021 --> 01:10:46.589
will start moving.
Once they start moving,

01:10:46.589 --> 01:10:49.287
it's like a pendulum with the
initial momentum,

01:10:49.287 --> 01:10:51.678
or energy.
It can climb up to the top and

01:10:51.678 --> 01:10:54.174
convert the potential to
kinetic, or kinetic to

01:10:54.174 --> 01:10:56.997
potential.
There is no loss of energy in

01:10:56.997 --> 01:11:00.363
that process.
Therefore, if you extract this

01:11:00.363 --> 01:11:04.582
velocity and took ½ (M +
m) times this velocity

01:11:04.582 --> 01:11:09.270
squared, you may in fact equate
that to (M + m)gh.

01:11:13.140 --> 01:11:16.930
So, let me summarize this last
result.

01:11:16.930 --> 01:11:19.409
In every collision,
no matter what,

01:11:19.409 --> 01:11:23.189
momentum is conserved;
the energy may or may not be.

01:11:23.189 --> 01:11:25.646
And if I give you a problem
like this where in between

01:11:25.646 --> 01:11:28.194
there's some funny business
going on which is not energy

01:11:28.194 --> 01:11:30.584
conserving,
don't use energy conservation

01:11:30.584 --> 01:11:33.430
from start to finish.
Use momentum conservation,

01:11:33.430 --> 01:11:35.829
find the speed of the composite
object.

01:11:35.829 --> 01:11:38.650
This is what you've got to
understand in your head.

01:11:38.650 --> 01:11:41.134
It's not this equation.
When can I use Conservation of

01:11:41.134 --> 01:11:43.050
Mechanical Energy?
When can I not?

01:11:43.050 --> 01:11:45.555
A bullet driving into a chunk
of wood, you better know you

01:11:45.555 --> 01:11:47.489
cannot use Conservation of
Kinetic Energy.

01:11:47.489 --> 01:12:06.770
But once the combination is
going up, trading kinetic for

01:12:06.770 --> 01:12:08.103
potential, you can.
 

